Robert CLARK v. UNITED STATES of America. No. 4857. Circuit Court of Appeals, Seventh Circuit. Oct. 6, 1932. , George R. Jeffrey, U. S. Atty., of Indianapolis, Ind., for appellee.

Before ALSCHULER, EYANS, and SPARKS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On motion of counsel for appellee, it is now here ordered and adjudged by this court that this cause be docketed in this court, and that this appeal be, and the same is hereby, dismissed, pursuant to section 1 of rule 14 of the Rules of this court.
